text: James Moulton Keck (September 4, 1921 â€“ June 25, 2018) was an American Air Force lieutenant general. He was born in Scranton, Pennsylvania. Keck's last assignment was vice commander in chief, Strategic Air Command, headquartered at Offutt Air Force Base, Nebraska. He served this position from October 1, 1973 and served until June 30, 1977. He served as commander of 2nd Air Force. Keck died on June 25, 2018 in San Antonio, Texas from complications of a broken hip at the age of 96. ==References== ==Other websites== * Biography Category:1921 births Category:2018 deaths Category:Deaths from fractured hip Category:American military personnel of World War II Category:American military personnel of the Korean War Category:American military personnel of the Vietnam War Category:People from Scranton, Pennsylvania Category:Military people from Pennsylvania
